{"questionId":"9073210","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">X has a capacitance of 18 μF. X is charged so that the one plate has a charge of 48 μC. X is then connected to an uncharged capacitor Y and a resistor via an open switch S.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/f473b51cb26197f728b9e3ee1fa52124309a698e.png\" width=\"254\" height=\"182\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Suggest why the answers to (a) and (b)(ii) are different.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">charge moves/current flows «in the circuit» ✔<br>thermal losses «in the resistor and connecting wires» ✔<br></span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE: Accept heat losses for MP2</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073210","referenceCode":"19N.2.HL.TZ0.9c","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Suggest why the answers to (a) and (b)(ii) are different.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.3 – Capacitance","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}